aim holds.\n- I independently confirmed the spine/body split underpinning 'a new kind never touches provenance attachment': rblds_Spine.sh:19-24 states the spine 'Owns NO kind knowledge' — a kind authors a recipe (step rows) + an opaque substitutions blob, and the :rbi_vouch push lives in the shared recipe-level rbgjl02 step. So the recommendation's file-disjointness / no-collision-on-provenance argument is sound."
    }
  }
]

