      "verdict": "Mostly accurate on structure but NOT shippable as-is: two high-severity problems. (1) The cost figures (~937K tokens, ~200 tool calls, ~8 min) are absent from the result artifact — it carries only agentCount: 10 and an empty logs list; the lone ~900K number is a 'rbfd:912,...' file:line citation, not tokens. Source or remove them. (2) The memo's explanation of the per-kind-verb false positive is wrong: the verbs were handed to every investigator in the script's SHARED prompt (line 57), and the verifier flagged them as fabricated because verifyPrompt omits that shared vocabulary, not because 'the subagents never received the paddock.' Everything else checks out and is well-supported: 10 agents (5 investigate + 5 verify via pipeline, not barrier), the claim/evidence/confidence + recommendation_input schema, and the four caught items (byte-equivalent overstatement with the rbi_es/rbi_ld locator split, over-assigned trust grades pinned to only bole+podvm, citation slips in augur/vertical/provdocs, and the verb false positive). Single most important fix: correct or source the cost figures, and fix the false-positive root-cause story."
